Bank of Japan Leaves Benchmark Rate Near Zero, Credit Programs Unchanged

-- B y   M a y u m i   O t s u m a
-- 
2011-04-28T04:31:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/bank-of-japan-leaves-benchmark-rate-near-zero-credit-programs-unchanged.html
The  Bank of Japan (8301)  held the
benchmark interest rate at a range of zero to 0.1 percent and
kept unchanged a 30 trillion yen ($366 billion) credit program
and a 10-trillion yen asset-purchase fund that represent its
main policy tools. The central bank announced its policy
decision in a statement today in Tokyo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mayumi Otsuma in Tokyo at 
 motsuma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ken McCallum at 
 kmccallum4@bloomberg.net  